# Sigma Fork Conventions

This repo is a fork of `AtomicBot-ai/atomicbot` (remote `upstream`).
We pull upstream updates periodically, so **minimizing merge conflicts is critical**.

## Directory Strategy

All new Sigma-specific code MUST live in dedicated `sigma/` directories.
Upstream will never touch these paths, so they merge cleanly.

### Renderer (frontend)

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `renderer/src/ui/sigma/` | Sigma-specific pages and components (local LLM panel, custom main view) |
| `renderer/src/store/slices/sigma/` | Sigma-specific Redux slices (local LLM state, server status) |
| `renderer/src/hooks/sigma/` | Sigma-specific React hooks (useServerControl, useModelDownload) |

### Main process (backend)

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/main/sigma/` | Sigma-specific services (llama.cpp download, model management, server manager) |
| `src/main/ipc/sigma/` | Sigma-specific IPC handlers (server-ipc, download-ipc) |

### Shared

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/shared/sigma/` | Sigma-specific IPC channels and types |

### Assets

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `assets/sigma/` | Sigma-specific assets (versions.json for llama.cpp/models, icons) |

## Upstream Files — Modification Rules

When you MUST modify an upstream file (routes.ts, store.ts, register.ts, preload.ts, app-bootstrap.ts):

1. Keep changes **minimal** — add imports and one-line registrations, nothing more
2. Mark Sigma additions with `// sigma:` comment prefix so they're easy to spot during merge
3. Prefer **appending** over inserting in the middle of the file

Example for `routes.ts`:
```ts
// upstream routes stay untouched above
  terminal: "/terminal",
  // sigma: local LLM routes
  sigma: "/sigma",
} as const;
```

Example for `register.ts`:
```ts
// sigma: register local LLM IPC handlers
registerSigmaIpc(deps);
```

## Files Owned by Sigma (merge=ours via .gitattributes)

These upstream directories are replaced by Sigma and upstream changes are auto-discarded:
- `renderer/src/ui/chat/**` — replaced by Sigma UI
- `renderer/src/ui/sidebar/**` — replaced by Sigma UI
- `renderer/src/store/slices/chat/**` — replaced by Sigma state

## Do NOT

- Put new Sigma code directly into upstream directories (`ui/settings/`, `main/gateway/`, etc.)
- Delete upstream files — replace their contents or leave them if unused
- Rename upstream files — it creates unresolvable merge conflicts
